arStrings.szText: Enh? Whassat? I'm paid up. Leave me be.
Annoyed. Groggy. Someone just woke you up from a narcotic-induced sleep
We're not here to collect. We need--
Hmm? It can’t be… can it? Is that the symbol of the Ho... Hora... uh...
groggy, confused. You're seeing a symbol pinned to a visitor's cloak you barely remember from your youth
Yes! Horadrim! Deckard? Deckard Cain?! Can it be you, old friend? It’s me! Meshif!
No, Deckard is gone. My name is Lorath. We need your help passing through the sandstorm to the north.
Sandstorm, eh? The others must’ve turned you down. Told you some rubbish about a sorcerer I’ll wager! (cackles)
extremely amused. You're the worlds funniest man
Well, what can a sorcerer do to me that time hasn't already! (laughs) Yes, yes! I’ll help! There's an old chapel near there, an auspicious spot to begin a new adventure!
Good. Gather whatever you need. I'll fetch Taissa and meet you there.
The last two sentences are spoken to the player
Ah! This is wonderful! Like old times, eh, Deckard?
